{
  "texts": [
    "The radar chart in Fig. 9 displays the user satisfaction distribution.",
    "The experimental group shows an advantage in three dimensions: feedback accuracy (4.6/5), response speed (4.5/5), and increased learning motivation (4.3/5).",
    "In contrast, the control group's traditional methods (gray line) scored below 3.5 in all areas.",
    "Figure 10 illustrates the writing development trajectory of a B1-level learner (according to the CEFR standard) over three months.",
    "The number of sentence types used by the learner increased from 4 to 9, and the usage of compound sentences rose from 12 to 37%."
  ]
}